The paper focuses on developing a neural network model for interpretable visual question answering, which involves reasoning on a dependency tree parsed from the question. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach for global reasoning on the dependency tree, which involves attention, composition, and propagation modules, indicating that the paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
